Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art on rock face (sandstone?), showing a single, schematic human figure painted in white pigment, a man, standing upright and facing left with an elongated torso, short legs and arms and a small erect penis. A 5cm scale bar has been fitted at the base of the image. Wadi Anak, Egypt. Scanned
Curator's comments: This site is a long, sloping shelter running up and under the protected side of an inselberg.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
